      • getCPUTime

        public static double getCPUTime​(long nflop,
                                int numPartitions,
                                IOCostUtils.IOMetrics executorMetrics,
                                RDDStats output,
                                RDDStats... inputs)
        Computes an estimate for the time needed by the CPU to execute (including memory access) an instruction by providing number of floating operations.
        Parameters:
        nflop - number FLOP to execute a target CPU operation
        numPartitions - number partitions used to execute the target operation; not bound to any of the input/output statistics object to allow more flexibility depending on the corresponding instruction
        executorMetrics - metrics for the executor utilized by the Spark cluster
        output - statistics for the output variable
        inputs - arrays of statistics for the output variable
        Returns:
        time estimate
